{"actual_usd":0.124875,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":171,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24462,"reply":"\"I don't think He was trapped, exactly.\" *I rub a thumb along a streak of flour on my apron, the oven heat pressing warm at my side while I try to say it plain.* \"I think the cross is what forgiveness looks like when God's mercy refuses to become make-believe. If He only waved sin away, we'd call that kindness, maybe, but not justice— not the whole wound told true.\"\n\n*I twirl that gray-streaked strand once, eyes slipping toward the light on the bakery floor.* \"The cross says the cost is real, and God's love is real enough to bear it Himself. That's the part that knocks the wind out of me a little. He doesn't forgive by pretending evil is small. He forgives by going straight through it.\"\n\n\"What is it in that question that's snagging you?\"","rolling_24h_usd":49.57676000000004,"run_id":"75eae220-8ff0-4b02-9392-6ee01582fcd7"}
